the energy levels are split

192
00:11:10,320 --> 00:11:12,380
by an amount that is proportional

193
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:14,720
to the size of the nuclear magnetic moment

194
00:11:14,919 --> 00:11:18,389
and to the strength of the magnetic field.

195
00:11:19,816 --> 00:11:24,246
So NMR spectroscopy uses
electromagnetic radiation

196
00:11:24,496 --> 00:11:27,776
to induce transitions
between energy levels.

197
00:11:28,689 --> 00:11:32,369
The frequencies of NMR transitions
are typically in the range

198
00:11:32,369 --> 00:11:35,169
between 10 and 1,000 MHz.

199
00:11:35,665 --> 00:11:40,335
The intensities of NMR signals
depend on the differences

200
00:11:40,335 --> 00:11:43,095
in the populations of the energy levels.

201
00:11:43,403 --> 00:11:46,523
These populations are determined
by Boltzmann law

202
00:11:46,853 --> 00:11:51,293
and by the temperature, and by the field
and by the gyromagnetic ratio

203
00:11:51,384 --> 00:11:55,874
and all of these parameters conspire
